sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as Istio Gateway<br/>(Envoy Proxy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant ExtProc as payload-processing<br/>(ext_proc)<br/>9004/TCP gRPC plaintext
    participant BFH as body-field-to-header<br/>plugin
    participant MPR as model-provider-resolver<br/>plugin
    participant AT as api-translation<br/>plugin
    participant AKI as apikey-injection<br/>plugin
    participant NemoReq as nemo-request-guard<br/>plugin
    participant NemoSvc as NeMo Guardrails<br/>Service
    participant NemoResp as nemo-response-guard<br/>plugin
    participant Provider as Cloud Provider<br/>(OpenAI/Anthropic/Azure/<br/>Bedrock/Vertex)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,Provider: Flow 1: External Model Inference Request

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Client auth (per Gateway config)
    Gateway->>ExtProc: ext_proc request body<br/>gRPC/9004 plaintext

    Note over ExtProc,AKI: Plugin Chain Processing (ordered)

    ExtProc->>BFH: Process request body
    BFH-->>ExtProc: Set X-Gateway-Model-Name header<br/>(from body.model field)

    ExtProc->>MPR: Process request
    Note right of MPR: Reads modelInfoStore<br/>(in-memory, from<br/>ExternalModel reconciler)
    MPR-->>ExtProc: Set CycleState:<br/>provider, model, credentialRef

    opt NeMo Guardrails enabled
        Note over NemoReq,NemoSvc: Flow 2: NeMo Input Guard Check
        ExtProc->>NemoReq: Process request
        NemoReq->>NemoSvc: POST /v1/guardrail/checks<br/>HTTP, configurable port
        NemoSvc-->>NemoReq: 200 OK (status: allowed/blocked)
        alt Request Blocked
            NemoReq-->>ExtProc: 403 Forbidden
            ExtProc-->>Gateway: Reject request
            Gateway-->>Client: 403 Forbidden
        end
        NemoReq-->>ExtProc: Allow (continue chain)
    end

    ExtProc->>AT: Process request
    Note right of AT: Translates OpenAI format →<br/>provider-native format<br/>(Anthropic Messages, Azure,<br/>Bedrock, Vertex AI)
    AT-->>ExtProc: Mutated body + path rewrite

    ExtProc->>AKI: Process request
    Note right of AKI: Reads secretStore<br/>(in-memory, from<br/>Secret reconciler)
    AKI-->>ExtProc: Inject auth header<br/>(Bearer/x-api-key/api-key)

    ExtProc-->>Gateway: Mutated request<br/>(new body, headers, path)
    Gateway->>Provider: Translated request<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>API key in header

    Provider-->>Gateway: Provider response
    Gateway->>ExtProc: ext_proc response body

    ExtProc->>AT: Process response
    Note right of AT: Translates provider response →<br/>OpenAI format<br/>(strip provider fields)
    AT-->>ExtProc: Normalized response body

    opt NeMo Output Guard enabled
        ExtProc->>NemoResp: Process response
        NemoResp->>NemoSvc: POST /v1/guardrail/checks<br/>HTTP, configurable port
        NemoSvc-->>NemoResp: 200 OK (status: allowed/blocked)
        NemoResp-->>ExtProc: Allow/block decision
    end

    ExtProc-->>Gateway: Final response body
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response<br/>OpenAI-compatible format

    Note over Client,Provider: Flow 3 & 4: Background Reconciliation (continuous)

    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over ExtProc,K8sAPI: ExternalModel Reconciliation
        K8sAPI-->>ExtProc: Watch ExternalModel CRDs<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
        Note right of ExtProc: Updates modelInfoStore<br/>(in-memory cache)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over ExtProc,K8sAPI: Secret Reconciliation
        K8sAPI-->>ExtProc: Watch Secrets (bbr-managed=true)<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
        Note right of ExtProc: Updates secretStore<br/>(in-memory cache)
    end
